The user has a playlist on YT, script to downloaded on using yt-ldp
Saves all the music on a directory.

It reproduces with :
alias voice='nohup mpv --shuffle --input-ipc-server=/tmp/mpvsocket /home/jorge/Videos/music/voice/*.mp3 >/dev/null 2>&1 & disown; sleep 1; exit'

To stop the music it do it with:


#!/bin/bash
echo 'cycle pause' | socat - /tmp/mpvsocket


#!/bin/bash

mpv --input-ipc-server=/tmp/mpvsocket /home/jorge/Videos/music/*.mp3

then we remap those commands to some keys